Justin Maass is a name that resonates with the rodeo community. Born in 1975, Maass has made a name for himself as a professional tie-down roper, earning recognition and accolades for his exceptional skills.

This article delves into the life and career of this rodeo cowboy, providing insights into his journey, achievements, and personal life.

About Justin Maass

Justin Maass was born in 1975 in the small town of Giddings, Texas, where he continues to reside. Growing up in a town with a rich rodeo culture, Maass was naturally drawn to the sport.

He attended Wharton Jr. College in Wharton, Texas, where he first tried his hand at roping and was instantly hooked.

Early Life

Maass’s early life was spent in Giddings, Texas, where he developed a passion for rodeo. His first encounter with roping at Wharton Jr. College set the stage for his future career.

Despite the challenges and risks associated with the sport, Maass was determined to pursue his passion, leading him to become a professional tie-down roper.

Professional Career

Justin Maass began his professional rodeo career in 1996. He has since become a prominent figure in the rodeo community, particularly in the tie-down roping category.

Maass is an eight-time Wrangler National Finals Rodeo (WNFR) qualifier, a testament to his exceptional skills and consistent performance.

Early Career

Maass’s professional career began in 1996, and he has been a tie-down roper in the professional ranks since then. His journey was not without its challenges.

Success didn’t come easy at the beginning of his career, but a significant turning point came when he borrowed $500 from his grandparents to enter the Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo.

Maass won Houston that year, setting him on a path that led to eight Wrangler National Finals Rodeo (WNFR) qualifications and over a million dollars in professional earnings.

Justin Maass’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, we estimated his net worth of $1 million based on his career earnings.

Considering his successful career as a professional tie-down roper, including his eight Wrangler National Finals Rodeo (WNFR) qualifications and over a million dollars in professional earnings, it can be inferred that Maass has accumulated substantial wealth.

It’s important to note that the earnings of professional rodeo cowboys can vary greatly depending on their performance in competitions, sponsorships, and other income sources.

Therefore, while we can estimate that Maass’s net worth is likely significant, an exact figure cannot be determined without specific financial disclosures.

Career Earnings

Maass has earned significant prize money throughout his career from his rodeo performances. For instance, he finished the regular season in 2012 with $144,001, giving him a $20,000 lead in the world standings heading into the NFR. 

His career earnings have contributed significantly to his net worth.

Salary

Justin Maass is a professional rodeo cowboy who has made significant money throughout his career. As of the current date, his career earnings in the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) amount to $1,345,637.00.

It’s important to note that the earnings of a rodeo cowboy can vary widely depending on their skill level, the events they participate in, and the prize money available at each event.

Top-level rodeo cowboys like Maass can earn hundreds of thousands of dollars annually, while less experienced cowboys may earn closer to $20,000 to $30,000 annually.

Personal Details

Age

As of 2023, Justin Maass is 48 years old.

Career Stats

Rodeo Accomplishments:

  • 8-time qualifier for the National Finals Rodeo (NFR) -1999, 2000, 2003, 2005, 2008, 2009, 2012, and 2013 in Tie Down Roping.
  • Reserve World Champion Tie Down Roper in 2012
  • Texas Circuit Finals , 17-time qualifier!
  • Texas Circuit Champion 2 times.
  • Texas Circuit Average Champion 2 times

Large Rodeos Won:

  • Houston, Texas – 2 times
  • Denver, Colorado – 2 times
  • Greeley, Coloardo – 2 times
  • Dodge City, Kansas – 2 times
  • Prescott, Arizona – 2 times
  • San Antonio, Texas
  • Austin, Texas

FAQs About Justin Maass

Where was Justin Maass born?

Justin Maass was born in Giddings, Texas.

When did Justin Maass start his professional career?

Maass started his professional career as a tie-down roper in 1996.

How many times has Justin Maass qualified for the WNFR?

Maass has qualified for the WNFR eight times.

What is Justin Maass’s net worth?

The exact net worth of Justin Maass is not publicly available, but he has earned over a million dollars in professional earnings.

How old is Justin Maass?

As of 2023, Justin Maass is 48 years old.

Conclusion

Justin Maass’s journey in the rodeo world is a testament to his passion, dedication, and resilience. From his humble beginnings in Giddings, Texas, to becoming a renowned professional tie-down roper, Maass’s story inspires aspiring rodeo cowboys and fans alike. Despite the challenges and uncertainties of the sport, Maass’s success underscores the rewards of perseverance and commitment to one’s passion.
